OL,3,CHurricane Melissa: How to support the
OL,4,Caid effort in Jamaica
OL,6,FThe UK government is also working with
OL,7,Fthe World Food Programme and the Red
OL,8,FCross to provide emergency relief to
OL,9,Fthe areas that need it most.
OL,11,FThe government originally committed up
OL,12,Fto #2.5 million to support
OL,13,Fhumanitarian response to support the
OL,14,FCaribbean region's recovery from
OL,15,FHurricane Melissa.
OL,17,FThis was later followed by an
OL,18,Fadditional pledge of #5 million in
OL,19,Femergency humanitarian funding, which
OL,20,Fincludes over 3,000 shelter kits and
OL,21,Fmore than 1,500 solar-powered lanterns.
